         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Office of Lands and Survey ¶ Melbourne. 15th Decr 1869. ¶ Sir, ¶  ¶ Referring to the correspondence which has taken place relative to the engagement of Mr Ferguson, I request you will be good enough a...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">69.12.15<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From James McKean</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Unit 3, p. 290, VPRS 7936/P1 outward letterbooks of the Secretary for Lands, Department of Crown Lands and Survey, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Office of Lands and Survey</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne. 15th Decr 1869.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Referring to the correspondence which has taken place relative to the engagement of Mr Ferguson, I request you will be good enough at once to recognize the position assigned to Mr Ferguson, as defined in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">Surveryor</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>General's letter of the 7th inst.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Letter not found</seg>.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">Check.</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>See also<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">x-ref letters from Lewis and McKean in the the prev. week.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">J. McKean to M 1 November had, as the Commissioner of Crown Lands and Survey, reported that he had instructed Ferguson to call on M to inspect the garden and see the works on which the men were employed.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">A. Skene to M, 7 December 1869, emphasized that the arrangements were not a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">judgement on his 'efforts and attainments in the more highly scientific branches of your Office', but intended 'to relieve you from active supervision of practical operations in the Garden'.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M apparently refused to do as asked when Ferguson arrived, and he was again instructed to do so in J. Lewis to M 10 December 1869.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and that you will without further correspondence, or difficulty, afford Mr Ferguson all information<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">necessay</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for his guidance in superintending, under your direction, the operations of the laborers and gardeners employed on your staff —</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most obedient Servant,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James McKean</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Commissioner of Crown Lands &amp; Survey<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">The same day</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">Also on 15 December<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>J. Lewis wrote to W. Ferguson directing him to 'proceed to Dr. Von Mueller's residence to receive your instructions from him accordingly.' (Unit 3, p. 290, VPRS 7936/P1, PROV).</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; color: #C00000; "
                        xml:lang="en">I assume that this refers to a letter of 15 ~December. With the addition of note 2 this is now not<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>immediately<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>clear.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Check my change is correct</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr F. Von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Government Botanist &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Botanic Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne.</p>
         </div>
